ptation and Community-based Water Management in Mékhé, Senegal -- t12. Flood Risk Preliminary Mapping in Niamey, Niger -- t13. Flood Risk Assessment at Municipal Level in the Tillabéri Region, Niger -- t14. Drought Risk in the Tillabery Region, Niger -- t15. Climate Change Adaptation Through Urban Planning: a Proposed Approach for Dar Es Salaam, Tanzania -- t16. Climate Change Adaptation in Dar es Salaam: Local Government Opinions and Proposed Interventions -- t17. Household Level Vulnerability to Climate Change in Nepal - A Comparison of a Semi-urban and a Rural Village Development Committee -- t18. Weather Observation Network and Climate Change Monitoring in Catalonia, Spain -- t19. Assessing flood risk in Zurich, Switzerland: the KR-RRA approach -- t20. Flood Risk Assessment and Quantification in the Piedmont Region, Italy -- t21. Conclusion0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aThis book provides examples of climate change characterization and decision-making tools for subtropical and tropical adaptation planning. It is intended for local operators, physical planners, besides researchers and students of these subjects. The first chapter describes the status of climate planning in large subtropical and tropical cities. The following six chapters discuss hazards (drought, intense precipitations, sea level rise, sea water intrusion) and early warning systems. Nine chapters enlarge on flood risk analysis and preliminary mapping, climate change vulnerability, comparing contingency plans in various scales and presenting experiences centred on adaptation planning. The last three chapters introduce some best practices of weather and climate change monitoring and flood risk mapping and assessment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access. Unless otherwise specified individually in the content, the work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attributio